{{Culture of Burkina Faso}} '''Burkinabé cuisine''', the '''[[cuisine]] of [[Burkina Faso]]''', is similar to the cuisines in many parts of [[West Africa]], and is based on [[staple food]]s of [[sorghum]], [[millet]], [[rice]], [[fonio]], [[maize]], [[peanut]]s, [[potato]]es, [[bean]]s, [[Yam (vegetable)|yam]]s and [[okra]].<ref name="ox">{{cite web | title = Oxfam's Cool Planet - Food in Burkina Faso | publisher = [[Oxfam]] | date = | url =http://www.oxfam.org.uk/coolplanet/ontheline/explore/journey/burkina/food.htm | accessdate =2008-05-21 }}</ref> Rice, maize and millet are the most commonly eaten grains.<ref name=foodculture>{{cite encyclopedia|article=Burkina Faso|encyclopedia=Food Cultures of the World|author=Liza Debrevic|pages=23–30|editor=Ken Albala|publisher=ABC-CLIO}}</ref> Grilled meat is common, particularly [[mutton]], [[goat]], [[beef]] and [[Fish (food)|fish]].<ref name="JM">Marchais, p. 99</ref> Vegetables include, besides yams and potatoes, okra, tomatoes, zucchini, carrots, leeks, onions, beets, pumpkins, cucumbers, cabbage, sorrel and spinach.<ref name=foodculture/>
== Common dishes == [[File:Fufu.jpg|thumb|right|240px|A plate of [[fufu]] (right) accompanied with [[peanut soup]]]] [[File:LocationBurkinaFaso.svg|thumb|Location of [[Burkina Faso]]]]
*[[Tô (food)]] ([[Saghbo]] in [[More language|Mooré]]), cooled [[polenta]]-style cakes made from ground [[pearl millet|millet]], [[sorghum]] or [[maize|corn]]. The tô is served with a sauce made from vegetables such as [[tomato]]es, [[Bell pepper|pepper]]s, [[sumbala]] and [[carrot]]s, sometimes supplemented by a piece of meat like mutton or goat. Eaten by hand, this traditional dish is the staple of the Burkinabè diet.<ref name="JM" /> *[[French green bean]]s *[[Fufu]] *Poulet Bicyclette, a grilled [[chicken (food)|chicken]] dish common across West Africa.<ref name="JM" /> *[[Ragout d'Igname]] *[[Riz gras]], rice cooked with onions, tomatoes and meat.<ref name=foodculture/><ref name="JM" /> *[[Riz Sauce]] *[[Sauce gombo]], a sauce made with [[okra]]. *[[Brochette]]s *Poulet Braisé, grilled chicken very popular in the city, almost all restaurants and bars propose that dish.
Restaurants generally serve Burkinabé dishes alongside those of neighbouring countries. Foreign dishes include a fish or meat stew called [[kédjénou]] from [[Côte d'Ivoire]] and [[poulet yassa]], a chicken stew with [[lemon]] and onions from [[Senegal]].<ref name="JM" />
<gallery class="center" caption="" widths="220px" heights="160px"> File:Baobab seeds.jpg|The fruit of the [[Adansonia|African Baobab]] tree File:Foods being cooked in Burkina Faso, Africa.jpg|Foods being cooked in Burkina Faso S.abderhalden4.jpg|Preparing tö </gallery>
==Common beverages== *[[Bissap (drink)|Bissap]]/Bisap, a sour-tasting drink made from [[Roselle (plant)|Roselle]] (Bissap) flowers,<ref>Grubben, p.321</ref> and sweetened with sugar *[[Degue]], a [[drink]] made from [[pearl millet]] and [[yogurt]] *[[Dôlo]], a [[beer]] made from [[pearl millet]] or [[sorghum]]<ref>Steinkraus, p.273</ref> *[[Toédo]], [[Adansonia digitata|Baobab fruit]] *[[Yamaku]] or Gnamankoudji, beverage made of [[Ginger]] *[[Zoomkoom]], a [[soft drink]] made from millet flour, [[ginger]], [[lemon]] juice and [[tamarind]]<ref name="ox" /> *Tamarin,
==See also== * [[Togolese cuisine]] * [[List of African cuisines]] {{Subject bar|portal1=Burkina Faso|portal2=Food}}
