{{Infobox airline | image_size = | airline = Canaryfly | image = Canaryfly_logo.svg | IATA = PM | ICAO = CNF | callsign = CANARY | aoc = | hubs = [[Gran Canaria Airport]] | focus_cities = | frequent_flyer = | alliance = | destinations = 6 | company_slogan = | parent = |num_employees=| alt = | founded = 2010 | commenced = | ceased = | bases = | secondary_hubs = | lounge = | subsidiaries = | headquarters = [[Gran Canaria]], [[Spain]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | profit = | assets = | equity = | website = [http://www.canaryfly.es/ canaryfly.es] }}
'''Canaryfly,'''([[IATA]] : '''PM''', [[ICAO]] : '''CNF''') is a Spanish airline that operates regular flights between the Canary Islands. == History == {{Advert section|date=March 2017}} Canaryfly was founded in 2008 operating flights between Canary Islands and Africa. in May 2012, Canaryfly started its first inter-island route (between different island of the Canary archipelago)
Canaryfly is led by Régulo Andrade and has more than 150 employees in 20 departments.
== Fleet == The Canaryfly fleet consists exclusively of [[ATR 72|ATR72]] turboprop aircraft.
==Routes== Canaryfly serves the following routes ( March 2017):<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.canaryfly.es/CNF/informacion.php |title=DESTINOS Y SUGERENCIAS |author= CanaryFly |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date= June 11, 2016 |quote=}}</ref>
