==Racial==
In terms of [[race (human categorization)|race]], the  demographics of South America shows a mixture of [[Europeans]], [[Anusim]] or [[Marrano]]s, [[Arabs]], [[Amerindians]], [[Africans]] and to a smaller extent [[East Asians]]. A mixture of Amerindian and European ancestry is often referred to as [[mestizo]] or caboclo/mameluco. [[Castizo]]s are people whose DNA is mostly European with Indigenous markers assimilation. A mixture of Amerindian and African ancestry is referred to in many South American countries as [[zambo]] or cafuzo. A mixture of European and African ancestry is referred to as [[mulatto]]. A mix of European and Japanese is referred as [[Eurasian (mixed ancestry)|ainoko]] or [[hafu]]. Chile administers [[Easter Island]] in the South Pacific, which is home to 2,500 Polynesians, the Rapa Nui people. 

