{{italic title}}
{{about|a newspaper in the Democratic Republic of the Congo|the municipality in Québec, Canada|L'Avenir, Quebec}}

'''''L'Avenir''''' is a [[daily newspaper]] published in [[Kinshasa]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].  The [[company]] is part of the [[Groupe L'Avenir]], a [[media group]] of the DRC. The content of the paper is primarily [[French language|French]], and includes content written in [[Lingala]] and [[Swahili language|Swahili]].  It was founded in 1996 as a weekly, and in 2006 became a daily paper, employing about 300 [[journalist]]s.

The publisher of ''L'Avenir'' is Joachim Diana Gikupa and the [[editor-in-chief]] is Denis Lubindi. 

