{{Portal|Catholicism}}

'''Richard Joseph Fitzgerald''' (1881–1956) was an [[Irish people|Irish]]-born [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[prelate]] who served as the [[Roman Catholic Bishop of Gibraltar|Bishop of Gibraltar]] from 1927 to 1956.<ref name=bfitz>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|bfitz|Bishop Richard Joseph Fitzgerald|27 May 2014}}</ref>

Born in [[Midleton]], [[County Cork]], Ireland on 12 August 1881, he was [[Holy Orders|ordained]] to the [[Priesthood (Catholic Church)|priesthood]] on 15 August 1905.<ref name=bfitz/> He was [[Appointment of Catholic bishops|appointed]] the [[Bishop (Catholic Church)|Bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gibraltar|Diocese of Gibraltar]] by [[Pope Pius XI]] on 25 May 1927.<ref name=bfitz/> His [[consecration]] to the [[Episcopal polity|Episcopate]] took place on 9 October 1927; the principal [[consecrator]] was the Most Reverend John Harty, [[Archbishop of Cashel]], with the Most Reverend James Roche, [[Bishop of Ross (Ireland)|Bishop of Ross]] and the Right Reverend [[Peter Amigo]], [[Archbishop of Southwark|Bishop of Southwark]], serving as co-consecrators.<ref name=bfitz/>

Bishop Fitzgerald died in office on 15 February 1956, aged 74.<ref name=bfitz/>

