'''''The Bishop of Lovech''''' ({{lang-bg|Ловчанският владика}}) is a Bulgarian comedy play by [[Teodosiy Ikonomov]], considered the first Bulgarian play. Ikonomov wrote it in 1857 as a student in Constantinople,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lapni.bg/offer/7933|title=Постановка  –  Васил Василев|publisher=Lapni.bg|accessdate=15 May 2015|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> in response to the lack of Bulgarian works being available, but it was not published until 1863 in [[Bolgrad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitsvishtov.com/landmarks.php?id=4&info=10&lg=en|title=Dates and facts|publisher=The official website for tourism of the town of Svishtov|accessdate=15 May 2015}}</ref> due to poor finances. The play is narrated from the viewpoint of Petko Slaveykov, who relates the struggle for independence of the Bulgarian church.

