'''Ásmundur Einar Daðason''' (born 29 October 1982) is an [[Iceland]]ic [[politician]]. He was a member of the [[Althing]] for the [[Northwest Constituency]] from 2009 to 2016 – first for the [[Left-Green Movement]] (VG), later for the centrist [[Progressive Party (Iceland)|Progressive Party]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ásmundur Einar Daðason|url=http://www.althingi.is/cv_en.php4?ksfaerslunr=121|publisher=Alþingi|accessdate=17 May 2012}}</ref>
He has also been the leader of the organisation Heimssýn, which gathers Iceland’s EU opponents.<ref>http://www.nordiclabourjournal.org/artikler/portrett/portrait-2018/article.2018-02-07.1627737317</ref>
On November 30, 2017, he became Minister of Social Affairs and Equality.<ref>https://www.government.is/government/</ref>
