{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Use British English|date=February 2018}} {|{{Infobox ship begin |display title=ital}} {{Infobox ship image | Ship image= | Ship caption= }} {{Infobox ship career | Hide header = | Ship name = ''Moorstone'' 1919-51; ''Kurtaran'' 1951-62; ''Çıkaran'' 1962-present | Ship namesake = | Ship owner = | Ship operator = [[Royal Navy]] 1919-51; M.Azmi Alpmen 1951-62; M.Taviloglu 1962-present<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship registry =*{{navy|United Kingdom}} *{{flagicon|Turkey}} [[Istanbul]] |Ship identification =*[[International Maritime Organization|IMO]] number 5072773; call sign TCCI *{{ICS|Tango}}{{ICS|Charlie}}{{ICS|Charlie}}{{ICS|India}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://shipping-data.com/ship/cikaran |title=Cikaran |author= |date= |work=Shipping Data |publisher= |accessdate=2011-05-22}}</ref> | Ship route = | Ship ordered = | Ship builder = [[Bow, McLachlan and Company|Bow, McLachlan & Co]],<ref name=Clyde>{{cite web |last1= Cameron |first1= Stuart |last2=Asprey |first2=David |title=HMDYC Moorstone |work=Clyde-built Database |publisher= |date= |url=http://www.clydesite.co.uk/clydebuilt/viewship.asp?id=12960 |accessdate= 2011-05-22}}</ref> [[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]], Scotland | Ship original cost = | Ship yard number = 380<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship way number = | Ship laid down = | Ship launched = 1919<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship completed = | Ship christened = | Ship acquired = | Ship maiden voyage = | Ship in service = 1919<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship out of service = | Ship fate = | Ship status = in service as of 2003<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship notes = }} {{Infobox ship characteristics | Hide header = | Header caption = | Ship class = ''Moor'' class | Ship type = mooring & [[salvage tug]]<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship tonnage = 459 tons [[Gross register tonnage|GRT]]<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship displacement = | Ship length = {{convert|139|ft|5|in|m|abbr=on}}<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship beam = {{convert|29|ft|1|in|m|abbr=on}}<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship height = | Ship draught = | Ship draft = | Ship depth = | Ship decks = | Ship deck clearance = | Ship ramps = | Ship power = [[triple-expansion steam engine]] | Ship propulsion = screw<ref name=Clyde/> | Ship speed = | Ship capacity = | Ship crew = |Ship armament = | Ship notes = }} |} '''''Çıkaran''''' is a ''Moor''-class mooring and [[salvage tug]]. [[Bow, McLachlan and Company]] of [[Paisley, Renfrewshire|Paisley]] in [[Renfrewshire]], Scotland built her for the [[Royal Navy]], who commissioned her as HMDYC ''Moorstone'' in 1919.<ref name=Clyde/> In 1948, she was decommissioned and, in 1951 she was sold to civilian owners in [[Turkey]], who renamed her ''Kurtaran''.<ref name=Clyde/> In 1962, she was sold again and her new owners named her ''Çıkaran''.<ref name=Clyde/> She was still in service in 2003.<ref name=Clyde/>
